text: Faither@Today's the day you start the school, isn't it?
Faither@I remember my time at school, I used to get into fights all the time.
Faither@You're not the biggest kid son, you're very skinny.
Faither@If one of those boys starts at you, you have to hit them back.
Faither@You'll come out it sore, but you can't let people walk over you.
Faither@Remember that, and you'll be alright.
Faither@Have you seen my _____ any where?
Faither@Help me find my _____ and we can leave.
Faither@Maybe your mother knows where I left it.
Faither@You've found it! Good stuff, thanks son.
Faither@Right, let's get you to school.
